  "sections": {
    "Background": {
      "text": "Definition: involuntary, irregular multidirectional  saccadic eye movements.\n[1]\nOccurs at fixed gaze and has been reported with various medication overdoses such as\norganophosphates\n,\nlithium\n, cetirizine, amitryptiline, and\ndiphenhydramine\n.\n[2]",
